course.subject: CPEG
course.name: Computer Engineering Final Year Project in ELEC
course.description: Each student of the Computer Engineering program is required to complete a final year project before graduation. The student is expected to conduct a project on a topic related to Computer Engineering and/or its application. The project is guided and conducted under the supervision of faculty members from the Department of Electronic and Computer Engineering. Credit load will be spread over the year. Instructor's approval is required for enrollment in the course. For CPEG students only.
